  • Method Details

    • getInternal

      gregtech.api.capability.IEnergyContainer getInternal()

    • acceptEnergyFromNetwork

      long acceptEnergyFromNetwork(crafttweaker.api.world.IFacing enumFacing, long voltage, long amperage)
      This method is basically changeEnergy(long), but it also handles amperes. This method should always be used when energy is passed between blocks.
      Parameters:
      enumFacing - given side
      voltage - amount of energy packets (energy to add / input voltage)
      amperage - packet size (energy to add / input amperage)
      Returns:
      amount of used amperes. 0 if not accepted anything.

    • inputsEnergy

      boolean inputsEnergy(crafttweaker.api.world.IFacing enumFacing)
      Parameters:
      enumFacing - given side
      Returns:
      if this container accepts energy from the given side

    • outputsEnergy

      boolean outputsEnergy(crafttweaker.api.world.IFacing side)
      Parameters:
      side - given side
      Returns:
      if this container can output energy to the given side

    • changeEnergy

      long changeEnergy(long differenceAmount)
      This changes the amount stored. This should only be used internally (f.e. draining while working or filling while generating). For transfer between blocks use acceptEnergyFromNetwork(IFacing, long, long)!!!
      Parameters:
      differenceAmount - amount of energy to add more than 0 or remove less than 0
      Returns:
      amount of energy added or removed
